                <head>164. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Jimmy Carter</persName> visited Riyadh
                    January 3–4, 1978, as part of a larger ten-day international trip that included
                    stops in Poland, Iran, India, Egypt, France, and Belgium. On January 3,
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> met with Saudi officials on
                    two occasions in order to discuss the Middle East peace process. For the
                    memoranda of conversation of these meetings, see <ref
                        target="frus1977-80v08#d183">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1977–1980, vol. VIII, Arab-Israeli
                        Dispute, January 1977–August 1978, Documents 183</ref> and <ref
                        target="frus1977-80v08#d184">184</ref>.</p>
            </div>
